body: The result of me trying to understand how packet handling in tox works. This change is a noop, really. I built `qtox`, `utox`, `toxic`, and `toxvpn` against this. All compile and, it seems, work as before. --- This change isâ€‚[](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/962)

@oxij There are some style issues that need to be fixed before this passes Travis: https://travis-ci.org/TokTok/c-toxcore/jobs/403915817
I'm not really happy with the new header that comes without a .c file. Are you planning to factor out code from net_crypto.c into net_packet.c?
Why: because we usually have 1 module = 1 .c + 1 .h file.
I'd prefer it merged, and build proper abstractions instead.
Done.
Generally looks good. What do you think of the size vs. end-start idea?

> Maybe it's better to define this number in terms of `END - START`.

That would be `END - START + 1`, which looks complicated, those lines will also get long. I like it the way it is.

> MSI is for toxav.

Ah, I see, I overlooked that. Removed that comment, added a comment to MSI message.

> Can you link to the commit? Why is it a hack?

Updated the comment.
Looks good, please rebase, then I'll merge it.
I've rebased it, since you hadn't signed your commits, so I had to do that anyway.
Ok. Thanks.
